<id>https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1463&amp;p=1564#p1564</id>
<link href="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1463&amp;p=1564#p1564"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Family • Fearing for your children’s future? Have Taqwa of Allah]]></title>

<category term="Family" scheme="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewforum.php?f=27" label="Family"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1463&amp;p=1564#p1564"><![CDATA[
Fearing for your children’s future? Have Taqwa of Allah<br /><br />Allah the Exalted said:<br /><ul>And as for the wall, it belonged to two orphan boys in the town; and there was under it a treasure belonging to them; and their father was a righteous man<br />(Soorah Al-Kahf 18:82) </ul><br />Allah the Exalted sent Musa and Al Khidr to rebuild the wall for the two orphan boys without payment, based upon the righteousness of their father.<br /><br /><ul>Ibn Abbas said: “They were protected due to the righteousness of their father and it is not mentioned that the two boys were righteous.” (Al Hakim 3395)<br /><br />Ibn Rajab said: Saeed Al Musayib said to his son: “O my dear son surely I increase in my prayer for your sake, hoping you will be protected.” Then he recited the verse: “And their father was a righteous man”.  <br /><br />Umar ibn Abdul Aziz said: “There is no believer who dies except that Allah will protect his offspring, and their offspring and their offspring.” <br /><br />Ibn Al Mukadir said: “Verily Allah will protect—by way of a righteous man—his children, and his children’s children and the homes around him. They will continue to be under Allah’s protection and cover. </ul><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">(Jaami' al-Uloom wal Hikam)</span></strong><br /><br />Rasheed ibn Estes Barbee <br /><br />Source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://mtws.posthaven.com/fearing-for-your-childrens-future-have-taqwa-of-allah">http://mtws.posthaven.com/fearing-for-y ... a-of-allah</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Tue Jul 11, 2017 12:05 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
